Text: Introductions. How am I, I am not too bad all things considering, thank you. My name is Liza Bobbi. How old am I, I am in my mid 50s.

Reason for visit. The reason I have come for a sight test today is because I am experiencing pain around my right eye with, glare and headaches. My GP advised that I come for an eye test because of my symptoms. The headaches are mainly on the right side near my temple and often in the evening. The pain, glare and other symptoms have been building up over the last few weeks. I thought the headache would go away, but it was really bad last night. I called the GP and they have advised me to get an eye test at my local optician. I normally take paracetamol for the headaches, but it doesn√ït really help, and I experience pain along with my headache sometimes. That is the main reason I am here, a real bad pain around my right eye and sometimes glare from bright lights.

Other symptoms. I struggle to read small print even when I'm wearing my reading glasses. I have not had any other symptoms other than the damn pain in my right eye recently. I don√ït have eye strain or redness. I do get the occasional floaters in my vision, I have had them for years now and I haven't noticed much of a change, the floater come and go. I mainly see the floater in the afternoons. I do not have any flashing lights.

Last eye examination and optical correction. My last eye test examination was 3 to 4 years ago. I got my reading glasses when I last had my eyes tested but now, even with those, I find myself struggling to read small print. My distance vision is fine. I don't have any glasses for my distance vision, I can see well in the distance without spectacles. I only have reading glasses.

My ocular history and my previous eye problems. I don√ït think I have eye problems such as macular disease, AMD, cataracts or glaucoma. I was seen at the eye hospital about 6 months ago because of Guillain Barre syndrome. I have been told that Guillain Barre syndrome is pretty rare, it effected my peripheral nerves. The orthoptists were seeing me at the hospital because one of my eyes was wondering and occasionally I was getting double vision. The double vision didn't last long, just a few days really. I don't have double vision now. I am having a check up with the orthoptists in 3 months time.

Family ocular and medical history. My family, my mother, brother and sister all have thyroid problems. My mother has high cholesterol as well. My father has an eye condition called glaucoma and he also has low blood pressure. There are no other eye problems in my family. No one in my family has heart problems or diabetes.

My general health. My general health has been pretty good apart from the Guillain Barre syndrome and thyroid problems. I don√ït have diabetes, high blood pressure or high cholesterol. I don√ït have any allergies. But, I do have an underachieve thyroid. I was hospitalised for a few days when my Guillain Barre syndrome was really bad 6 months ago. I have been told that Guillain Barre syndrome is pretty rare, it effected my peripheral nerves. I am now discharged from the hospital, but I am being seen by the orthoptics clinic as one of my eyes was wandering and I was seeing double for a while. I was told my eye muscles aren√ït very active and my next check-up with the orthoptist is in 3 months.

My medication. I take tablets called levothyroxine for my underactive thyroid. I also take Gabapentin, melatonin, paracetamol and ibuprofen because I was hospitalised for Guillain Barre syndrome about 6 months ago, so I am still taking those tablets to reduce pain and to help me sleep at night.

My occupation and hobbies. For a living, work, I am not working now as I am still recovering from the Guillain Barre syndrome. When I was working last year, I was a manager at a local supermarket. It was quite a fun job working with lots of people, I miss them now, but hope to be able to get back to work soon once I am fully over this wretched Guillain Barre syndrome thing. Overall, I spend about 4 hours a day looking at screens, mostly the TV or my mobile phone. I don't have a computer.

My hobbies. I do have some hobbies including exercise and yoga to keep healthy. My favourite yoga teacher is Adriene, her YouTube channel is fantastic. I also like watching TV as well, but that's not really a hobby. Mostly I just watch soaps and sometimes those reality TV shows like 'love island'. I drive.
Anything else. I don√ït smoke, but I do drive. I don't have contact lenses. I don't want contact lenses. I have nothing else to add. I have nothing more to tell you.
